25|$|On the European Tour, the ANZ Championship, {{which ran}} {{for three years}} from 2002, used the same {{modified}} <b>Stableford</b> scoring system as The International. The Investec Royal Swazi Open on the Sunshine Tour has used the same system since 2003. Two Champions Tour events also used the modified <b>Stableford</b> system briefly. They were the Royal Caribbean Classic in 2000 and 2001, and the Uniting Fore Care Classic in 2002. In the latter case, it {{was seen as a}} final attempt to save the failing tournament.|$|E
